Package: corrcat
Type: Package
Title: Correlation matrix for categorical variables 
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Zhi Lin Zhou
Maintainer: Zhi Lin Zhou <lilyzhi.zhou@mail.utoronto.ca>
Description: Calculates the correation coefficient between categorical variables using Cramer's V.
    Produces a table of correlation coefficients and a correlation matrix for categorical variables in the dataset.
    This packages does not detect which variables are categorical so user will need subset the data to only categorical variables of interest beforehand. 
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
URL: https://github.com/lilyzhizhou/corrcat
BugReports: https://github.com/lilyzhizhou/corrcat/issues
Imports: 
    corrplot,
    RColorBrewer,
    rcompanion
